{
  "texts": [
    "While most toolkits are not designed for unethical usage, there is often potential for abuse in their applications.",
    "In our demo (Section 4), we apply our toolkit to train RQA systems based on documentations obtained from two companies' website, Databricks and Faire.",
    "However, since our toolkit can be used with any kind of data, it is possible to use it for unethical tasks, such as scamming and generating harmful responses (Gehman et al., 2020; Welbl et al., 2021).",
    "We do not condone the use of LOCALRQA for any unlawful or morally unjust purposes.",
    "Many existing toolkits, such as Haystack, LangChain, and LLamaIndex help users quickly build an RQA system (Pietsch et al., 2019; Chase, 2022; Liu, 2022)."
  ]
}